{
  "texts": [
    "Table 1 shows the weighted F1-scores of the zero-shot LLMs with generic prompts on all datasets, fine-tuned LLMs evaluated on sampled test sets of the data, and VADER on all data.",
    "Even without substantial prompt engineering or annotated examples to the zero-shot LLMs, GPT3.5-Turbo outperformed VADER on four out of five datasets and FLAN-T5 outperformed VADER on three out of five datasets.",
    "Though zero-shot LLMs have demonstrated higher performance than VADER, their results are still far from usable for research on most of the datasets, with weighted F1-scores lower than 0.6.",
    "The LLMs achieved the highest performance on the Vitals dataset, with a weighted F1-score of 0.97.",
    "Notably, both GPT3.5-Turbo and FLAN-T5 have extremely poor performance on the HPV and HCR data."
  ]
}